comments: Drummond (PHI) reaches for the ball and avoids contact with Morant's (MEM) arm during his drive to the basket.
Thybulle (PHI) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as his hand slides off of Morant's (MEM) front during the drive.
Morant (MEM) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two steps after his gather.
Drummond (PHI) brings his arm down and makes contact with Morant's (MEM) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) is already in Williams' (MEM) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Drummond (PHI) is already in Williams' (MEM) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) is moving alongside Thybulle's (PHI) path to the basket and he legally contests Thybulle's driving shot attempt.
Adams (MEM) is already in Thybulle's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Drummond (PHI) slides his hand across Morant's (MEM) arm, causing Morant to momentarily lose control of the ball, which he quickly recovers.
Bane (MEM) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot and he slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Drummond (PHI) is already in Morant's (MEM) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Drummond (PHI) loses control of the ball on his own prior to any contact from Jackson Jr. (MEM).
Curry (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he begins to imminently exit the lane.
Harris (PHI) jumps forward into Morant's (MEM) body and initiates contact as Morant is passing the ball.
Drummond (PHI) re-establishes himself slightly in Morant's (MEM) path and marginal contact occurs as Drummond is firming up.
Morant (MEM) moves alongside of Curry (PHI) and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) turns slightly towards the basket and marginal contact occurs as Maxey (PHI) commits to going under the pick.  Jackson Jr. then absorbs the ensuing contact.
Maxey (PHI) cleanly ties up Bane (MEM) as he defends the driving shot attempt, and a jump ball is correctly called.
Morant (MEM) dribbles the ball with his right hand and brings his left hand to the ball without taking another dribble.
Drummond (PHI) is in the paint for longer than three seconds before the shot is imminent.
Green (PHI) is moving alongside Morant's (MEM) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.

Morant (MEM) extends his arm out to the ball and incidental contact occurs as he brushes Drummond's (PHI) face during the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Morant (MEM) commits a take foul on Drummond (PHI).
Williams (MEM) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI).

Replay review of the foul called on Drummond (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Drummond jumps from A to B and makes contact with Morant's (MEM) body and arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) and Harris (PHI) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Bane (MEM) is established in Curry's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the transition play up the court.

As Curry (PHI) drifts away from the basket, his momentum carries him backwards towards Jackson Jr. (MEM), who otherwise would avoid making contact with Curry.  The marginal contact is caused by Curry.
Williams (MEM) and Harris (PHI) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Drummond (PHI) brings his hand forward and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Bane's (MEM) arm as he passes the ball.
Adams (MEM) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Philadelphia.
Bane (MEM) and Curry (PHI) briefly engage and disengage as they come together during the screen.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) makes clean contact with the ball prior to making any contact with Maxey (PHI).  Any ensuing contact after the shot is blocked is considered incidental.
Adams (MEM) is already in Maxey's (PHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Morant (MEM) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps after his gather.
Maxey (PHI) avoids making any foot to foot contact with Morant (MEM), who loses his balance on his own at the end of the drive.
Drummond (PHI) brushes Morant's (MEM) body and marginal contact occurs as Morant stumbles forward on his own during his driving shot attempt.
Drummond (PHI) cleanly blocks Morant's (MEM) shot attempt before it has reached its apex and is on its downward flight towards the basket.
During the rebound, Williams (MEM) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Curry (PHI) as Williams' hand slides off of the ball.
Williams (MEM) and Harris (PHI) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as they cleanly tie up the rebound. A jump ball is correctly called.
Harris (PHI) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) contests Harris' (PHI) shot attempt and marginal contact occurs after Harris has released his shot attempt.
Adams (MEM) is already in Maxey's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Curry (PHI) briefly grasps and immediately releases Williams' (MEM) jersey and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Possession is awarded to Philadelphia.  Drummond (PHI) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession should have been awarded to Memphis.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) absorbs the contact from Maxey (PHI) and avoids making contact with his head during his contest on the driving shot attempt.
Thybulle (PHI) steps slightly forward towards Morant (MEM) and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Niang (PHI) steps forward into Morant's (MEM) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR at the end of the drive.
Morant (MEM) establishes his left foot as his pivot, which he slides after he receives the pass.
Thybulle (PHI) steps slightly towards Morant (MEM) and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Maxey (PHI) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Morant's (MEM) body as he passes the ball.
Green (PHI) legally contests Williams' (MEM) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) grabs and pulls Harris' (PHI) jersey away from his body in order to get to the ball, which affects Harris' ability to secure the rebound.
